what to hunt, spellcasting techniques, or guides to low level equipment.<br><br>Trepidae has the majority of her level 1 and 4 spells, barring those I felt were not of any immediate urgency (True North, Cold Light, Sense the Dead and Numb the Dead).  The only armor she currently has is her starting robe (2AC).  She was rewarded with a Vellium great staff after collecting spiderling silks for a Master Tailor.  She has amassed a little over 40pp selling extra stacks of bone chips and HQ bear pelts to other players.  Yes, a necro *selling* bone chips...what a rebel! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Should I be looking to buy better equipment at this point, or should I wait and save for spells?  I know that level 8 is going to be rough.  11 spells, all of which I think are important, and all of which cost over 4pp each!  I never realized how rough you caster classes had it! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ukaymarrandomacts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaymar RandomActs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member<br><font color=blue>Olympics Champion</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/21/01 5:47:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Baby Necromancer</span><hr size=1> Sense the dead is really useful <p><img src="http://www.morosa.f9.co.uk/kaymar.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ubalamurstoutfaith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balamur Stoutfaith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span>